P.Span: Select a Deployment from the drop-down menu to filter the information. By default, your report displays information for all deployments. The drop-down menu also indicates the number of flows in each deployment.

The Deployed Flows table lists the deployed flows found in the deployments. Determine which characteristics of the deployed flows are most important to you. If more than one scheduling server contains deployed flows, filter by the associated scheduling server to view only the deployed flows executed by that scheduling server.
Trigger events are associated to the deployed flow, not a particular deployed job. When a trigger event filter is applied, the Deployed Jobs table is empty.

NOTE: Profiling deployed flows searches the SAS Metadata Server for platform objects. In the case of Platform LSF scheduling, the Platform Suite for SAS must have been installed and used for metadata objects to have been created. If a user did not install this software, then profiling will not find Platform objects. Platform Suite for SAS was most recently available with SAS Grid Manager for Platform.

The flows represented on this page have been gathered using flow definition files exported from IBM Spectrum LSF Process Manager,10.1.0 or later, from SAS 9 Platform Suite for SAS. The definition files must have been created by an administrator and made
available
to Content Assessment prior to executing the profile.

A "(Missing)" event condition usually indicates the flow, or job, must be manually triggered. An "lsf" event condition indicates the trigger is based on the job status returned by the LSF master host.

Span.Span: The Deployed Flows value shows the number of deployed flows found in all deployments.
The Scheduling Servers value shows the number of unique scheduling servers in all deployments.
The Total Jobs value shows the number of SAS Data Integration Studio jobs associated with the deployed flows in all deployments.
The Scheduled Flows value shows the number of deployed flows that have been submitted to the scheduling server.
The Flows with Dependencies value shows the number of deployed flows that have dependencies on other jobs.
The Flows with Triggering Events value shows the number of deployed flows that have events to trigger the flow execution.

The SAS 9 Profile for SAS Data Integration Scheduling report enables you to explore the scheduling details of SAS Data Integration Studio deployed flows, including SAS 9 Platform Suite for SAS flows. Information such as the scheduling server, triggering conditions, and dependencies are available, as well as the SAS Data Integration Studio jobs that are part of the flow. If you are interested in additional objects or more technical details, see
SAS 9 Profile for SAS Data Integration

P.Span: This report provides a breakdown of the SAS Data Integration Studio deployed flows so you can identify any scheduled job inputs and outputs that will need to be planned for as you migrate SAS Data Integration Studio jobs to a SAS Viya environment.

P.Span: Content Grouping.

Some companies organize their data in their SAS systems according to data governance rules. These rules might prescribe a pattern in the file system directory or metadata folder structure. At some level of the directory or folder structure, it is reasonable to assume that the data is being collected into a logical grouping. These groupings are helpful when planning for a migration because they organize the data into smaller and more focused collections.

In this report, the grouping Full Program Name displays the directory or folder structure of each SAS program file. By default, this grouping is the fourth level of the directory or folder structure. You can edit the level using
to change the grouping that is displayed. The specified setting groups report content and displays the grouped results by that level of the directory or folder structure.
For example, the default content grouping in /opt/SAS/projects/HR/payroll/ would be "HR".
A job is a collection of SAS tasks that create output.
Deployed Flow.
A deployed flow is a group of jobs and their dependencies, including dependencies on other jobs, on files, or on specified dates and times.
Scheduling Server.
A scheduling
server is a server that runs deployed jobs in a scheduled deployed flow. The scheduling server determines whether conditions and dependencies have been met before a job is run.
Deployed Job.
A deployed job is a
job that has been saved in a deployment directory and can be scheduled.
SAS 9 Platform Suite for SAS Flow

. A SAS 9 Platform Suite for SAS flow is a SAS deployed flow converted to an IBM Spectrum LSF Process Manager flow definition. These flows are created in SAS 9 and scheduled using a Platform Process Manager server. ​​​​​​
The report design might not be updated in each release. The design was last updated in Version 2025.01.

SAS has made every attempt to ensure that the information in this report is accurate. Our commitment is to continue to enhance this application. Please check the SAS 9 Content Assessment documentation for changes.

Span.Span: Which jobs have deployed flows that can be scheduled?

Select a deployed flow from the top table to view its deployed jobs. Triggers that initiate a deployed job to run and dependencies are listed in the bottom tables. Trigger events can be age, day, date, file-based, and so on. A deployed flow's associated jobs are important because deployed flow migration depends on associated jobs completing successfully.
